  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Stop Hunger Now works to support the development efforts of Hope for Angola by providing meals for crisis relief and medical programs in Angola.

Hope For Angola is a 501(c)(3) non governmental organization founded by Angolans living in the United States to respond to social and economic problems faced by the people of Angola, especially those in the most vulnerable groups. This shipment will support the Angolan people who are suffering from a two year-long drought. According to the United Nations, 1.8 million Angolans have been affected by the drought in ten of the fourteen provinces and among them, a third of the affected are children. For this particular shipment, the focus is to assist 25,000 drought affected people in the province of Cunene, namely the localities of Cahama, Otchinjau, Xangongo and Ondjiva. The meals will also support a medical clinic in Odjiva.</narrative>
